<i>Posted by Ysgwyrthyr on 12-22-2000 03:54 AM:</i>

<p><b><img src="images/icons/Disco_Ball_Face.gif" alt="" width="15" height="15" border="0"> </b></p>

<p>You have to press yourself into the wall <b>beside</b> Trooper Mojo, as far away from the entrance as possible, to hand in bone-chips and avoid a 2 second death to the Crusaders.  Get ready to hand in 4000+ bonechips to get dubious to CrusadersOfGreenmist faction.<br>
<br>
Now that VI has fixed the secondary faction bug, anyone should be able to become non-kos in Cabilis.  The Mojo quest doesn't do necro faction (BroodOfKotiz) but that's only a problem with West Cabilis and one part of East Cabilis (a tavern on the right side of the canal looking away from the shaman guild has a necro inside called Grype).<br>
<br>
To raise necro faction, you have to kill Iksar Bandits, Marauders, Manslayers, Pariahs, Exiles, etc (and LOTS of them).<br>
<br>
I did this as a 40th Cazic-worshipping troll shaman and had to hand in 4000 bonechips to get my faction up.  Best way to get bone-chips is to buy them while slaughtering skeles (with pet <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="">) in Kurn's Tower.  Most people in there are ~15th level and are more than happy to <b>give</b> you every chip they get in exhange for shaman buffs (particularly chloro, tuna and alacrity!)  Even so, it took me 40 hours online collecting bonechips to get 4000 of the buggers.  Cabilis is worth it though... you can:<br>
<br>
 - BANK!!!<br>
 - cut down travelling time<br>
 - buy food, water; sell gear<br>
 - train and buy spells<br>
 - do iksar quests!  (hehe, I like this one <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt=""><br>
<br>
Hope that helps.<br>
<br>
Ysgwyrthyr Balor, <i>(soon ta be)</i> <b>da Mystic Troll</b><br><FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><br>
