<i>Posted by Aktunka on 12-22-2000 11:32 PM:</i>

<p><b><img src="images/icons/Dizzy_Face.gif" alt="" width="15" height="15" border="0"> Pretty thorough walkthrough</b></p>

<p>Ok I am a troll shaman that worships Inno, and I did this way back when kunark was just released. The factions will be listed below along with what I consider the best ways to raise them.<br>
<br>
First of all, the factions and who they correspond to...<br>
<br>
Legions of Cabilis--------Troopers and Warrior guild<br>
Scaled Mystics------------Shaman guild<br>
Crusaders of Greenmist----SK Guild<br>
Swifttails (i think hehe)-Monks Guild<br>
Cabilis Residents---------Bankers, most vendors in<br>
                          east cabilis, some vendors<br>
                          in west cabilis, various others<br>
                          especially in east cabilis.<br>
Brood of Kotiz------------Necros, Most Vendors in west<br>
                          cabilis (including alchemy)<br>
<br>
Lots of things will raise legions faction, but only thing I have found so far that raises Brood of Kotiz faction, as another poster pointed out, are the iksar bandit types. (Footpad, bandit, manslayer, etc.) My recommendation if you are just starting out on cabilis faction is to kill iksar bandit types exclusively if you can. This will raise the all important legions faction (needed for most of the faction quests that are easy to do) as well as the necro faction. This is good because you will then be non kos in west cabilis as well after you finish the faction quests, and also because they sell muffins and milk in west cab <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt=""><br>
<br>
The bone chip quest in FoB is offered by Trooper Mogo at the cab entrance. You can be relatively close to him, but should definitely be as close to the wall as possible to avoid aggro from crusaders. Also, be warned...if you think you are close to finally being non kos with the crusaders, do not make the judgement based on /con of Crusader Quarg....he is some slightly strange faction so that you can actually be dubious with him, yet still threateningly by Crusader Bodli and all others. If you do the bone chips quest all the way through making Crusader Bodli dubious to you, then you will be non kos to almost all of east cabilis. If you are an agnostic, you probably will be non kos to all, unless you didn't work on necro faction, then yes, Grype will kos you, but he is only up in the upstairs of the Tink and Bauble (sp?) during the nightime (in-game) hours. If you are a worshipper of Inno, like myself, then at this point you will still be KOS with the bankers, 2 iksars at the hut right by the bank (ones name is Jozter), Haggle Baron, and Haggle Baron's assistant guy (upstairs in Tink and Bauble in Grype's place during daylight in-game hours). <br>
<br>
Anyhow that is how it works, so working up till apprehensive with crusader bodli would be recommended to make sure that you are probably high enough faction that nothing in east cab will kos you. Good luck, and sorry if this started rambling...because I seomtimes start rambling hehe<br>
<br>
Aktunka Wormflinger<br>
Lvl 55 Troll Shaman<br>
Drinal</p>
