<i>Posted by Fulaq on 01-15-2001 05:48 PM:</i>

<p><b> Confusion reigns :)</b></p>

<p>As far as I know there is nothing in Dreadlands that will lower your brood of Kotiz faction, sarnaks will lower your brood of Dizok faction, which is a different thing entirely.  So that might be what you were noticing Torvo.<br>
<br>
The forsaken (Bandits etc...) give you one faction point per kill, so from start you need to kill 2000 to get to indifferent in West cabilis.<br>
<br>
Once you get all your bonechips and Forsaken killing done you should be:<br>
<br>
Necro's indifferent<br>
Merchants indifferent<br>
Monks amiable<br>
Shaman amiable<br>
Warriors kindly/warmly<br>
Sk's amiable<br>
<br>
There are no other factions in Cabilis, you will be not KOS anywhere at all in the city and can wander freely, trade bank train etc. etc. etc.<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><br>
